Introduction¶

The objective of this project is to predict whether a patient is likely to get stroke based on the input parameters like gender, age, various diseases, and smoking status. The dataset was sourced from kaggle at https://www.kaggle.com/fedesoriano/stroke-prediction-dataset (fedesoriano, 2021).

This report is organized as follows:

  • Overview describes the dataset used and the features in this dataset.
  • Data Preparation section covers data cleaning and data preparation steps.
  • Data Exploration and Visualisation explores dataset features and their relationships.
  • Summary and Conclusion section provides a summary of our work and presents our findings.
  • References section provides list of refereces

Overview¶

Data Source¶

According to WHO, stroke is the second leading cause of death. Moreover, stroke is the major cause of disability This dataset is sourced from kaggle. It is used to predict whether a patient is likely to get stroke based on the input parameters like gender, age, heart disease, hypertension, average glucose level, and smoking status. Each row in the data provides relavant information about the patient. This dataset has 5061 observations with 11 columns having 1 target feature 'stroke'.

Project Objective¶

The objective of this project is to build a machine learning model which predicts whether a patient is likely to get stroke based on the input parameters like gender, age, heart disease, hypertension, average glucose level, and smoking status.

Target Feature¶

Our target feature is 'stroke' which is a binary variable. '1' meaning Yes, had a stroke and '0' meaning No stroke suffered

Descriptive Feature¶

  • id: unique identifier(Numerical)
  • gender: "Male", "Female" or "Other"(Nominal Categorical)
  • age: age of the patient (Numerical)
  • hypertension: 0 if the patient doesn't have hypertension, 1 if the patient has hypertension(Nominal Categorical)
  • heart_disease: 0 if the patient doesn't have any heart diseases, 1 if the patient has a heart disease(Nominal Categorical)
  • ever_married: "No" or "Yes"(Nominal Categorical)
  • work_type: "children", "Govt_job", "Never_worked", "Private" or "Self-employed"(Nominal Categorical)
  • Residence_type: "Rural" or "Urban"(Nominal Categorical)
  • avg_glucose_level: average glucose level in blood(Numerical)
  • bmi: body mass index(Numerical)
  • smoking_status: "formerly smoked", "never smoked", "smokes" or "Unknown"(Nominal Categorical)
  • stroke: 1 if the patient had a stroke or 0 if not(Nominal Categorical)

Goals and Objectives¶

The objective of this project is to build a machine learning model which predicts whether a patient is likely to get stroke based on the input parameters like gender, age, heart disease, hypertension, average glucose level, and smoking status with high accuracy by selecting the best algorithm.

Summary and Conclusion¶

Exploratory data analysis was performed on stroke dataset. Firstly, we performed data preparation and cleaning in which we checked the data types of each attributes. We performed the sanity checks and then, checked for missing values. We handled those missing values by using mean technique. After this our data was ready for exploration and visualisation. Then, we observed various relationship between the variables and got more insights from our dataset.

We got these major insights:

  • More number of females can be seen to have suffered by stroke as compared to males.
  • Older people are more prone to suffer from stroke than younger people.
  • Higher amount of average glucose level increases your chance to have a stroke. People having average glucose level above 200 are diabetic which increases their chance of having a stroke.
  • Higher BMI does not indicate higher chances of having a stroke.
  • If a person has greater BMI, greater average glucose level and is old, their chance of having a stroke increases.
  • Old age people having hypertension or heart disease were seen to be suffering more by stroke than younger people

According to WHO, Stroke is the second leading cause of death. Taking look at our insights, it is found that the factors above do increase your chance of having a stroke so we should take care of our health by consuming balanced diet, exercising daily and more.
